'''击倒'''（'''{{lang|en|knockout}}'''），也称为'''击倒游戏'''（'''{{lang|en|knockout game}}'''）、“'''K.O.王'''”（'''{{lang|en|knockout king}}'''）、“'''轰炸'''”（'''{{lang|en|bombing}}'''）<ref name="uk1"/><ref name="uk2"/>、“'''打北极熊'''”（'''{{lang|en|polar-bearing}}'''、'''{{lang|en|polar-bear hunting}}'''）<ref name=nbcpolar /><ref name=nypostpolar /><ref name=cbspolar />，是2012年至2013年发现的主要在[[美国|美国]]黑人间流行的一种暴力袭击游戏<ref>{{cite web|title=街头暴力游戏在美蔓延 “毫无预兆一击就倒”|url=http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2013-11/26/c_125760504.htm|publisher=新华网 转载自《北京青年报》|accessdate=2013-11-30|archive-date=2013-12-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131208222603/http://news.xinhuanet.com/world/2013-11/26/c_125760504.htm|dead-url=no}}</ref> 。游戏参与者会随机选定行人或其他陌生人为目标，趁其不注意时冲到受害者身边施以重拳，力求一拳将受害者击昏倒地（一击K.O.）<ref name=nypostpolar /><ref>{{cite news |title=Unprovoked attacks at heart of 'Knockout King' |author= |url=http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/3d281c11a96b4ad082fe88aa0db04305/Article_2011-12-24-Thrill%20Assaults/id-ec1b19d37a334c6e909beb03e1b6237f |agency=Associated Press |date=2011-12-24 |accessdate=2013-11-30 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://www.webcitation.org/64J2wq7iH?url=http://hosted2.ap.org/APDEFAULT/3d281c11a96b4ad082fe88aa0db04305/Article_2011-12-24-Thrill%20Assaults/id-ec1b19d37a334c6e909beb03e1b6237f |archivedate=2011-12-30 }}</ref>。有的参与者会将过程拍摄下来上传至[[互联网|互联网]]。这种游戏已经导致多人重伤甚至死亡。某些发生击倒案例的市镇警方碍于[[逆向种族主义|逆向种族主义]]而声称所谓击倒游戏是[[都市传说|都市传说]]，是将某些零星袭击事件串联的结果，是一种[[道德恐慌|道德恐慌]]<ref>{{cite web|first=Melanie|last=Eversley|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/11/26/knockout-game-myth/3729635/|title=Reports: Alleged Trend of 'knockout game' a myth|publisher=USA Today|date=2013-11-26|accessdate=2013-11-29|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208021157/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/11/26/knockout-game-myth/3729635/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=slate>{{cite web |last=Roller |first=Emma |url=http://www.slate.com/blogs/weigel/2013/11/25/why_the_knockout_game_trend_is_a_myth.html |title=Why the "Knockout Game" trend is a myth |publisher=''Slate'' |date=2013-11-25 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2013-11-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131126044601/http://www.slate.com/blogs/weigel/2013/11/25/why_the_knockout_game_trend_is_a_myth.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。另外的看法则认为击倒游戏中有种族动机，是族群之间的[[仇恨犯罪|仇恨犯罪]]<ref name=slate /><ref name=times /><ref name=beast>{{cite web |last=Bouie |first=Jamelle |url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/11/25/guess-what-the-knockout-game-is-america-s-latest-phony-panic.html |title=Guess What? The 'Knockout Game' Is America's Latest Phony Panic |publisher=''The Daily Beast'' |language=en |date=2013-11-25 |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2013-11-27 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131127233511/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/11/25/guess-what-the-knockout-game-is-america-s-latest-phony-panic.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=snopes>{{cite web|url=http://www.snopes.com/politics/crime/montgomery.asp |title=Knockout Game Turns Deadly |publisher=Snopes.com |date=2013-09-27 |language=en|accessdate=2013-11-26}}</ref><ref name=msnphilly>{{cite web |url=http://news.msn.com/crime-justice/knockout-game-a-crime-trend-or-random-violence |title='Knockout game': A crime trend or random violence? |publisher=News.msn.com |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131129102549/http://news.msn.com/crime-justice/knockout-game-a-crime-trend-or-random-violence |archive-date=2013-11-29 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>。

==历程==
最早的类似击倒游戏的例子可以追溯到1992年<ref name=yngve>{{cite news|title=MIT student's death attributed to violent "knockout" game|url=http://news.google.com/newspapers?id=2pZGAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lvgMAAAAIBAJ&pg=6167,4733376&dq=violent+knockout+game&hl=en|language=en|accessdate=22 April 2011|newspaper=The Day|date=1992-09-23|archive-date=2020-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200630205133/https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=2pZGAAAAIBAJ&sjid=lvgMAAAAIBAJ&pg=6167,4733376&dq=violent+knockout+game&hl=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[英格兰|英格兰]]和[[法国|法国]]地区也有类似的案例<ref name="uk1"/><ref name="uk2" /><ref name=chicago>{{cite web |last=Moser |first=Whet |url=http://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/The-312/July-2012/Point-Em-Out-Knock-Em-Out-Knockout-King-Happy-Slapping-and-Random-Street-Violence/ |title='Point Em Out Knock Em Out,' 'Knockout King,' 'Happy Slapping,' and the Murder of Delfino Mora | Chicago magazine |publisher=Chicagomag.com |date=2012-07-18 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111215720/https://www.chicagomag.com/Chicago-Magazine/The-312/July-2012/Point-Em-Out-Knock-Em-Out-Knockout-King-Happy-Slapping-and-Random-Street-Violence/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。2013年中段，一个英国少年进行了一系列此类袭击。当时这种游戏被称为“轰炸”<ref name="uk1"/><ref name="uk2" />。舆论将这种行为和另一种源自英国的青少年街头犯罪“[[掴掌乐|掴掌乐]]”（{{lang|en|happy slapping}}，一种由数人将受害者围住进行掌掴取乐并用手机摄录的行为）联系在一起<ref name="chicago" />。

美国社会发现击倒游戏则源于有媒体发现了东北部地区有不断增长的此类攻击事件报告<ref name=times />。2013年11月，[[纽约|纽约]][[布鲁克林区|布鲁克林区]]的[[王冠高地|王冠高地]]（{{lang|en|Crown Heights, Brooklyn}}）地带发生了一系列连续袭击事件，导致传言扩散<ref name="jweek1">{{cite web |first=Jonathan |last=Mark |url=http://www.thejewishweek.com/news/new-york-news/knockout-attacks-concern-crown-heights |language=en |title='Knockout' Attacks A Concern |publisher=The Jewish Week |date=2013-11-20 |accessdate=2013-11-30 |archive-date=2013-12-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131203004757/http://www.thejewishweek.com/news/new-york-news/knockout-attacks-concern-crown-heights |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20131125/crown-heights/brooklyn-jewish-leaders-offer-1500-reward-for-knockout-game-arrests |title="Brooklyn Jewish leaders offer 1500 reward for knockout game arrests". ''DNA.info''. Nov. 25, 2013 |publisher=Dnainfo.com |date=2013-11-22 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-26 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131126054253/http://www.dnainfo.com/new-york/20131125/crown-heights/brooklyn-jewish-leaders-offer-1500-reward-for-knockout-game-arrests |archivedate=2013-11-26 }}</ref><ref name="DN CH">{{cite web |url=http://nydailynews.com/1.1514604 |title=NYPD investigating Crown Heights 'knockout' attacks on Jews as possible hate crimes - Daily News |language=en |publisher=Nydailynews.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2013-11-26 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20131126142825/http://nydailynews.com/1.1514604 |dead-url=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jewishpress.com/news/breaking-news/crown-heights-knockout-the-jew-attacks-serial-hate-crimes/2013/11/14/ |language=en |title=Yanover, Yoni. "Crown Heights Knockout-the-Jew attacks serial hate crimes". ''The Jewish Press''. Nov. 14, 2013 |publisher=Jewishpress.com |date= |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111194852/https://www.jewishpress.com/news/breaking-news/crown-heights-knockout-the-jew-attacks-serial-hate-crimes/2013/11/14/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>。有关击倒游戏成为流行的说法开始出现。这种说法被认为是一种都市传说，是青少年犯罪事件造成的[[道德恐慌|道德恐慌]]。<ref name=slate /><ref name=times /><ref name=beast /><ref name=snopes />
 
==成因==
击倒游戏的肇因很多。某些媒体评论将焦点集中在这些袭击行为中的种族成分上，另外也有舆论将其与其他非种族犯罪联系。

===“游戏”的说法===
在某些案例中，媒体将击倒袭击行为称为“游戏”，是暴力犯罪游戏的一种。这些行为中的“游戏”成分包括：随机选择受害者，有专门拍摄并上传至网络，录影中可以听到参与者的笑声等等。但也有认为这种行为并非“游戏”的看法。纽约市警方怀疑这种行为并非是流行趋势，只是数起独立犯罪事件的巧合<ref name=cnn>{{cite web |url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/11/22/justice/knockout-game-teen-assaults/ |title=Police keep close eye on reports of disturbing 'knockout' game - CNN.com |publisher=CNN |date=2013-11-22 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-30 |archive-date=2020-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111221438/https://edition.cnn.com/2013/11/22/justice/knockout-game-teen-assaults/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>不过纽约州众议员Jim Tedisco要求立法将“击倒游戏”定为可判刑范围，将制造这种袭击的青少年视为成年人处理。<ref name=cnn />[[纽约州|纽约州]][[锡拉丘兹_(纽约州)|雪城]]警方声称，他们在审问一起致命袭击的袭击者时，後者认定自己进行的是“击倒游戏”，并且只是在“玩游戏”，而不是[[谋杀|谋杀]]或抢劫<ref name=times>{{cite news | url=http://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/23/nyregion/knockout-game-a-spreading-menace-or-a-myth.html?_r=1& | title=Police Unsure if Random Attacks Are Rising Threat or Urban Myth | publisher=New York Times | language=en | accessdate=23 November 2013 | archive-date=2020-12-08 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208021612/https://www.nytimes.com/2013/11/23/nyregion/knockout-game-a-spreading-menace-or-a-myth.html?_r=1& | dead-url=no }}</ref>。据《纽约时报》11月23日报导，纽约市警方正考虑如何应对这种“游戏现象”，以及应当如何向市民提供建议，但仍然没有确定这种游戏的确实存在性。<ref name=times />不少官方人士拒绝将这种袭击行为认定为“游戏”。费城市长{{tsl|en|Michael Nutter|迈克尔·纳特}}（Michael Nutter）明确表明他不愿意将发生在当地的一起袭击定位为此类游戏。[[密歇根州|密歇根州]][[兰辛_(密歇根州)|兰辛]]市的“指出并击倒”（{{lang|en|point 'em out, knock 'em out}}）的袭击则使用了[[泰瑟枪|泰瑟枪]]。
 
===种族问题===
在2013年的袭击事件评论中，一些保守派的政治评论家将焦点集中在种族因素上。他们强调这类袭击多数是由[[非裔美国人|非裔]]青少年制造，并谴责媒体对其中的种族因素避而不谈。<ref name=susteren>{{cite web |url=http://nation.foxnews.com/2013/11/19/greta-knockout-game-no-laughing-matter-where-are-jesse-jackson-al-sharpton-and-others |title=Greta: 'Knockout Game' No Laughing Matter ... Where Are Jesse Jackson, Al Sharpton and Others? - Fox Nation |language=en |publisher=[[Fox_Nation|Fox Nation]] |date=2013-11-19 |accessdate=2013-11-30 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202234746/http://nation.foxnews.com/2013/11/19/greta-knockout-game-no-laughing-matter-where-are-jesse-jackson-al-sharpton-and-others |archive-date=2013-12-02 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>[[福克斯新闻频道|福克斯新闻频道]]的政治评论员[[比尔·奥莱利|比尔·奥莱利]]（Bill O'Reilly）将“击倒”袭击行为描述为“美国年青黑人无意义犯罪的又一个例子”并对“它们得到如此少的关注”感到失望。<ref>{{cite news|last=|first=|date=19 November 2013|language=en|title=The 'Knockout' game|url=http://www.foxnews.com/on-air/oreilly/2013/11/20/knockout-game|agency=Fox News Channel|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131127151343/http://www.foxnews.com/on-air/oreilly/2013/11/20/knockout-game|archivedate=2013年11月27日|accessdate=2013年11月30日}}</ref> 

{{link-en|约翰杰刑事法学院|John Jay College of Criminal Justice}}研究与评估中心的领导人杰弗里·巴茨（Jeffrey Butts）则称击倒游戏被置于种族的有色眼镜下审视。<ref name=times />《Slate》杂志的埃玛·罗勒（Emma Roller）和The Daily Beast的贾梅尔·鲍伊（Jamelle Bouie）认为在一系列击倒游戏的报导中，受害人是白人，袭击者是年少黑人的事实被过分强调了。他们认为[[YouTube|YouTube]]不能作为击倒游戏的可靠证据。<ref name=slate /><ref name=beast />此外黑人社群也对袭击作出谴责，并指出若受害者是黑人时他们将不会沉默<ref>{{cite web |last1=Roberts |first1=Georgett |last2=Gartland |first2=Michael |language=en |url=http://nypost.com/2013/11/23/al-sharpton-condemns-knockout-attacks/ |title=Al Sharpton condemns 'knockout' attacks | New York Post |publisher=Nypost.com |date=2013-11-23 |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2020-12-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201209230302/https://nypost.com/2013/11/23/al-sharpton-condemns-knockout-attacks/ |dead-url=no }}</ref>

===反犹===
布鲁克林区袭击中的8名受害者都是犹太人。有的人因此怀疑这些袭击是[[反犹|反犹太人]]的仇恨犯罪。<ref name=nbcpolar>{{cite web |url=http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Knockout-Game-Polar-Bearing-Hate-Crimes-Punch-Slap-Video-232695381.html |title=Police Added in Brooklyn Neighborhood Amid "Knockout Game" Attacks |publisher=[[WNBC|WNBC]] |date=2013-11-20 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-23 |archive-date=2013-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202230743/http://www.nbcnewyork.com/news/local/Knockout-Game-Polar-Bearing-Hate-Crimes-Punch-Slap-Video-232695381.html |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=nypostpolar>{{cite web |last=Velez |first=Natasha |url=http://nypost.com/2013/11/22/nypd-hate-crime-unit-probing-brooklyn-knockout-attack/ |title=Jewish man clocked in 'knockout' attack | New York Post |publisher=[[New_York_Post|New York Post]] |date=2013-11-22 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-23 |archive-date=2020-11-25 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201125023549/https://nypost.com/2013/11/22/nypd-hate-crime-unit-probing-brooklyn-knockout-attack/ |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=cbspolar>{{cite web |url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2013/11/22/4-men-arrested-in-alleged-knockout-attack-in-brooklyn/ |language=en |title=4 Men Arrested In Apparent 'Knockout' Attack In Brooklyn " CBS New York |publisher=[[WCBS-TV|WCBS-TV]] |date=2013-11-22 |accessdate=2013-11-23 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123045459/http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2013/11/22/4-men-arrested-in-alleged-knockout-attack-in-brooklyn/ |archivedate=2013-11-23 }}</ref>ABC Nightline报导，纽约市警方反犹太主义也是袭击的诱因之一。<ref name=nightline>{{cite web |url=http://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/sucker-punch-spike-knockout-game-attacks-21013587 |title=Sucker Punch: Possible Spike in 'Knockout Game' Attacks " ABC News |publisher=[[ABC_Nightline|ABC Nightline]] |date=2013-11-26 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2020-08-03 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803003228/https://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/sucker-punch-spike-knockout-game-attacks-21013587 |dead-url=no }}</ref>一名28岁的袭击者由于袭击犹太人，被以“仇恨犯罪”的罪名起诉，有可能面临比袭击罪名严重得多的判罚。<ref name=nbcpolar /><ref name=jweek1 /><ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.yahoo.com/knockout-game-suspect-charged-hate-crime-100039465--abc-news-topstories.html |title='Knockout Game' Suspect Charged With Hate Crime |last1=Fields |first1=Liz |last2=Mahoney |first2=Gillian |date=2013-11-24|website=Yahoo.com |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-24 |archive-date=2020-03-08 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200308003508/https://news.yahoo.com/knockout-game-suspect-charged-hate-crime-100039465--abc-news-topstories.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>这名袭击者否认自己是反犹太人主义者。<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.latinopost.com/articles/1340/20131125/knockout-attack-suspect-charged-with-hate-crime-says-hes-not-anti-semitic.htm |title='Knockout' Attack Suspect Charged With Hate Crime Says He's Not Anti-Semitic : Local |publisher=Latino Post |date=2013-11-17 |language=en |accessdate=2013-11-26 |archive-date=2013-11-28 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131128060629/http://www.latinopost.com/articles/1340/20131125/knockout-attack-suspect-charged-with-hate-crime-says-hes-not-anti-semitic.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref>

